# Polling Error Handling

When a weather API fetch fails for any reason:
- Log at WARNING level with these exact fields: city=<name>, status=<http_status_or_error_type>, attempt=<retry_count>
- Do NOT raise the exception — return None and let the scheduler retry on the next interval
- Example: logger.warning("Poll failed city=%s status=%s attempt=%s", city, e.response.status_code, attempt)

# Deduplication

All reading inserts must use INSERT OR IGNORE with the (city, timestamp) unique constraint.
Never check for existence before inserting — the DB constraint is the source of truth.
Check cursor.rowcount == 1 to determine if the insert was new.

# Logging levels
- New reading stored → INFO
- Duplicate skipped → DEBUG (not INFO — this happens every poll)
- Fetch failure → WARNING
- Event fired → INFO with event_type= and city= fields
